{
  "stem": "19111.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 262.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we heard the explosions, big explosions.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were not too far from Munich, maybe 20 miles or something.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were able to hear faint explosions from far away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we have surmised-- because we had-- we had no way of finding what was going on, what the war is like.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we have surmised that this must be either a Russian or American or British planes bombing Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that gave us a little bit more of a hope.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Somehow we have renewed hope that something is happening, that perhaps if we can hold on with our last bit of strength, maybe, maybe we can still make it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were days where I was outside there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was so hungry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was so starved that I actually pulled the grass from the foot-- from the ground and chewed on grass.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I looked up, and I counted the planes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were times that I counted up to 400 planes passing by and 500 planes another day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the bombings and all that-- I was sure that something is happening-- and just hold on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that gave me the idea, oh, God, if I can only survive this thing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If I can only find myself on the other side a free man and be able to sit at a table, look at a whole loaf of bread, be able to cut off a piece to eat, I'll never ask for more.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I'll, I'll be very satisfied and happy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SIGHS] That was 1944, and I was 15 years old.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I had gone through such hell, seen so much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But now, I was invigorated by what I saw up there in the sky.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
